# ============================================================
# EVENT CORE RUNTIME
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: runtime
domain: event
scope: event.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines core runtime handling for event.

## runtime_scope
Runtime covers event visibility,
event acceptance state,
event processing state,
replay rendering,
historical event reference,
and safe failure rendering.

## current_view_state
Runtime-visible event state must distinguish:
- accepted event
- processed event
- rejected event
- replayed event
- historical event

## validation_rules
- event identity must resolve
- source identity must resolve
- occurrence boundary must resolve
- payload scope must be valid
- replay/reference mode must be valid

## failure_modes
- invalid event identity
- invalid source scope
- invalid boundary scope
- invalid replay/reference mode
- safe runtime fallback

## observability
Runtime must emit enough signals
to distinguish acceptance,
processing,
replay,
historical reference,
and failure surface.

## review_checklist
- event runtime scope is explicit
- replay-aware rendering is explicit
- failure handling is explicit
